Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop them onto a large
#baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over the @mustard seeds{1%sachet}, season with @salt{}
and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway
through.

Meanwhile, remove the @slow cooked beef{280%g} from its packaging. Place in an #ovenproof dish{}
along with the juices and cover loosely with #foil{}.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure it's piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1/2}(halved, peeled and sliced thinly) as thinly
as you can.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the onion, @rice vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and a pinch of
@salt{}. Set aside to pickle.

Pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

In another medium bowl, combine the mint and @Greek style natural yoghurt{150%g}. Season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}, then set aside.

When the beef has 5 mins remaining, remove from the oven, reserve 1 tbsp of cooking juices
per person, then discard the foil and any remaining cooking juices.

Drizzle over the @Rogan Josh curry paste{50%g} and return to the oven for the remaining time,
~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, sprinkle the @plain naans{2%units} with a little water and pop them into the oven
to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the beef from the oven.

Stir through the reserved cooking juices, then use two #forks{} to shred the beef as finely
as you can.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Share the naans between your plates. Spread the mint yoghurt over the bases, then top with
the pulled beef and a few slices of pickled onion.

Add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the bowl of the remaining pickled onion, add a drizzle of
@oil{} and toss to combine.

Serve your loaded naans with the mustard seed potatoes and the salad alongside.

Drizzle the @mango chutney{40%g} over the beef to finish.

Enjoy!